===Noun===
'''inclination'''
#A [[tilt]] or [[bend]]
#* The '''inclination''' of his head increased and he awoke with a start.
#A [[slant]] or [[slope]]
#* The road up to the house had a steep '''inclination'''.
#A [[tendency]]
#* He had an '''inclination''' to drink.
{{wikipedia}}
#(''astronomy'') The [[angle]] of [[intersection]] of a [[plane]] and the [[orbital]] plane of a [[planet]] or [[moon]] etc; also the angle between an object's [[orbit]] and the [[ecliptic]]
